metadata.name: PixlFlippr #511
metadata.description:
PixlFlippr is an offshoot of my "Simple Harmonic Motion" series, inspired by the complexity of life emerging through the interaction of simple 'dumb' behaviors, with intricate details emerging on multiple scales. PixlFlippr operates on a pixel level (in the form of a GLSL frag shader).

Every pixel oscillates at a single fixed frequency, slightly out-of-sync with its neighbors. There is no explicit pixel-neighborhood communication (as there would be in eg Cellular Automata), and every pixel acts autonomously, oblivious to its surroundings. Yet collectively, the entire system exhibits constantly evolving complex high level behavior on many scales, ranging from patterns & behaviors spanning a few pixels, all the way up to the level of the entire image. These are further amplified through the emergent pixel aliasing artefacts & moiré patterns. 

Also, it's trippy af. 

PS All generative mints are a seamless loop with a loop duration ranging from a few minutes to over an hour. So stick around & watch it mutate!

metadata.name: HOPONO #223
metadata.description:
I’M SORRY / PLEASE FORGIVE ME / THANK YOU / I LOVE YOU
Ho'Oponopono is an ancient Hawaiian spiritual practice that involves learning to heal all things by accepting "Total Responsibility" for everything that surrounds us – confession, repentance, and reconciliation. 
This practice has been part of the French street artist Arthur Simony’s creation for a while, on paper, canvas… and now on the TEZ blockchain!
Original piece by Arthur Simony - October 2022 - Paris, France
Powered by David Ughetto @_dugh x Guillaume Horen @guillaumeh

metadata.name: gate maze #54
metadata.description:
Tragedy, confusion, childhood. All this comes together for me in this artwork. I do not consider myself a tragic person, but remembering my childhood and the problems that caused a lot of emotions, a colorful picture appears in front of me, overflowing with pain and notes of something new. 
  For someone new can be fatal, and this is probably the main flaw in the phrase "Learn from your mistakes."
  Lines that intertwine each other and create chaos native to me. I think everyone can find here something that will cause nostalgia.

metadata.name: Spaziotempo #88
Overlay #43
metadata.description:
Overlay is inspired by the double exposure of analog photography and the 4-Color Process screen printing technique, where images are superimposed, mixing their
colors to form new ones, shapes are also mixed, sometimes they look like mountains, sometimes waves.

The initial price at unlocking will be 12 xtz. every 5 minutes, it will be reduced by 3 xtz to the death price of 1 xtz.

metadata.name: Spaziotempo #92
Dencity #665
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

Kyoshin(虚心) means to be free from all bias, like frankness and open mindedness.

metadata.name: Sixty# #194
metadata.description:
This idea was born from recent discussion on generative art and the path the medium is finding for itself. The project aims to take aesthetic concepts from sci fi graphic novels and blend them with generative systems of abstraction. 

The debate is between using previously established art forms to influence this new medium, or using a new medium to meticulously reproduce a previous medium. I believe there’s room to explore the full spectrum, and I am attempting to find the midpoint that fits my work and brings me the most happiness.

The title describes the eventual aesthetic objective, which is to create a piece which might look like a splash page a colorist alone has been given the freedom to design and explore their own specialty. It explores centralized polar compositions, vibrant colors, plus lots and lots of movement. 60# paper is a standard weight for printing of comic books and graphic novels.

Press ’s’ in live view to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js
